The evidence with the title '1970s in Western fashion - Wikipedia ' says Fashion in the 1970s was about individuality. In the early 1970s, Vogue proclaimed "there are no rules in the fashion game now" due to overproduction flooding the market with cheap synthetic clothing. Common items included mini skirts, bell-bottoms popularized by hippies,  ... .. In Pakistan, Afghanistan and Iran, many liberal women wore short skirts, ... 
